tischen Gehaltes der Isonomie bedeutet. Das vorliegende Buch geht der Entwicklung des politischen Begriffs nach, d. h. von seinem Ursprung im 6. Jahrhundert v. Chr. bis in die römische Kaiserzeit.  aThis book examines the origin and development of the concept of "isonomia" along with theoretical concepts of order that extend across epochs from ancient times to the imperial age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aDemokratia. 4aGemeinsinn. 4aGemeinwohl. 4aIsonomia. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh  aCommon Good.  aDemocracy.  aIsonomy.  aParticipation.  aShareholding.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z97831107538130 cEPUBz97831107237620 cprintz978311071796940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072366340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110723663423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110723663.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075381-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK